# Zenn Article Guidelines

## File Naming
- Use the Zenn slug format for filenames
- Include semantic prefixes when possible (e.g., `017_what-is-embedding-in-generative-ai.md`)

## Content Structure
- Start with proper frontmatter (title, emoji, type, topics, published)
- Use clear, descriptive headings with proper hierarchy
- Include code examples with proper syntax highlighting
- Reference images from the `images/` directory

## Technical Content
- When writing about Mastra framework, reference actual implementation examples
- Use code snippets from [src/mastra/](mdc:src/mastra/) when relevant
- Explain concepts with practical examples
- Include proper error handling in code examples

## Zenn CLI Usage
- Use `npx zenn preview` for local preview
- Use `npx zenn new:article` for new articles
- Validate articles before publishing

## Images
- Store images in `images/` directory
- Use descriptive filenames matching article slugs
- Reference images using relative paths in markdown
